rossing%20movie%20of%202023.%3Cp%3EJaap%20Buitendijk%2FWarner%20Bros.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%26quot%3BBarbie%26quot%3B%20may%20have%20been%20the%20biggest%20hit%20of%202023%2C%20but%20its%20director%2C%20Greta%20Gerwig%2C%20is%20a%20rarity%20in%20Hollywood.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ETwo%20recent%20studies%20highlight%20progress%20for%20women%20directors%20and%20creatives%20behind%20the%20scenes%20has%20stalled.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAccording%20to%20USC%2C%20only%205.6%25%20of%20directors%20on%20the%20top%201%2C600%20films%20from%202007%20to%202022%20were%20women.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBarbie%26quot%3B%20may%20have%20been%20the%20highest-grossing%20movie%20of%202023%20and%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fhighest-grossing-movies-by-women-female-directors-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efirst%20film%20by%20a%20solo%20woman%20director%20to%20cross%20%241%20billion%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20its%20impact%20hasn't%20been%20felt%20in%20Hollywood%2C%20yet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20two%20recent%20studies%20on%20inclusion%20in%20Hollywood%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fassets.uscannenberg.org%2Fdocs%2Faii-inclusion-directors-2023.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUSC%20Annenberg's%20Inclusion%20Initiative%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwomenintvfilm.sdsu.edu%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F2023-Celluloid-Ceiling-Report.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESan%20Diego%20State%20University's%20Center%20for%20the%20Study%20of%20Women%20in%20Television%20and%20Film%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20progress%20for%20women%20directors%20has%20stalled.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESDSU's%20report%2C%20%26quot%3BThe%20Celluloid%20Ceiling%2C%26quot%3B%20has%20tracked%20the%20number%20of%20women%20employed%20in%20behind-the-scenes%20roles%20in%20the%20film%20industry%20for%20the%20last%2026%20years.%20Female%20directors%20accounted%20for%20just%2016%25%20of%20the%20250%20top-grossing%20movies%20this%20past%20year%2C%20down%20from%2018%25%20in%202022.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3B2023%20was%20a%20year%20in%20which%20things%20were%20not%20as%20they%20seemed%20in%20Hollywood%2C%26quot%3B%20Martha%20Lauzen%2C%20Ph.D.%2C%20the%20SDSU%20study's%20author%2C%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20the%20ultimate%20illusion.%20Greta%20Gerwig's%20well-deserved%20triumph%20belied%20the%20gender%20inequality%20that%20pervades%20the%20mainstream%20film%20industry.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUSC%20Annenberg's%20annual%20study%20looked%20at%20the%20top-grossing%201%2C600%20films%20from%202007%20to%202022%20and%20found%20that%20only%205.6%25%20of%20those%20directors%20were%20women.%20Only%2073%20individual%20women%20directed%20the%201%2C488%20highest-grossing%20movies.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20it's%20not%20just%20directors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20SDSU's%20study%2C%20in%20the%20last%20year%2C%2094%25%20of%20the%20top%20250%20films%20had%20no%20female%20cinematographers%2C%2086%25%20had%20no%20female%20composers%2C%2074%25%20had%20no%20female%20writers%2C%20and%2072%25%20had%20no%20female%20editors.%C2%A0Movies%20with%20a%20female%20director%20usually%20employ%20more%20women%20behind%20the%20scenes%2C%20the%20study%20found.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20you%20look%20at%20the%20data%2C%20these%20numbers%20have%20barely%20budged%20since%201998.%20It's%20sad.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFive%20years%20after%20Frances%20McDormand%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fwhat-frances-mcdormand-meant-by-inclusion-rider-in-oscar-acceptance-speech-2018-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eurged%20the%20industry%20to%20adopt%20inclusion%20riders%20in%20her%202018%20Oscars%20speech%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20mitigate%20Hollywood's%20representation%20problem%2C%20not%20much%20has%20changed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhite%20male%20directors%20benefit%20from%20repeat%20opportunities%20more%20often%20than%20women%20and%20people%20of%20color%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20report's%20authors%2C%20Stacy%20L%20Smith%2C%20Ph.D.%2C%20Katherine%20Pieper%2C%20Ph.D.%2C%20and%20Sam%20Wheeler%2C%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BHiring%20women%20and%20people%20of%20color%20more%20than%20once%20across%20popular%20motion%20pictures%20is%20one%20important%20solution%20for%20change.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20women%20get%20these%20opportunities%2C%20it's%20not%20always%20for%20a%20solo%20project.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnly%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fhighest-grossing-movies-by-women-female-directors-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Esix%20of%20the%20100%20highest-grossing%20movies%20of%20all%20time%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20were%20directed%20by%20women%2C%20a%20milestone%20that's%20minimized%20since%20the%20top%20three%20%E2%80%94%20%26quot%3BCaptain%20Marvel%2C%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3BFrozen%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3BFrozen%20II%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20were%20codirected%20by%20men.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20percentage%20of%20women%20directors%20didn't%20increase%20after%20%26quot%3BFrozen%2C%26quot%3B%20co-directed%20by%20Jennifer%20Lee%20and%20Chris%20Buck%2C%20became%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F2014%2Ffilm%2Fnews%2Ffrozen-becomes-the-highest-grossing-animated-film-ever-1201150128%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehighest-grossing%20animated%20movie%20of%20all%20time%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202014%20(only%20to%20be%20surpassed%20by%20its%20sequel.)%20Nor%20did%20it%20shift%20much%20after%20Patty%20Jenkins%20directed%2C%20arguably%2C%20the%20DC%20Extended%20Universe's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fjustice-league-dceu-movies-ranked-2017-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estrongest%20entry%20with%202017's%20%26quot%3BWonder%20Woman%2C%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20which%20became%20that%20year's%20top-grossing%20movie.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20biggest%20wins%20in%20the%20past%20few%20years%20is%20that%20female%20directors%20have%20been%20given%20the%20freedom%20to%20direct%20potential%20franchise%20films%20on%20their%20own%20without%20the%20co-credit%20of%20a%20male%20colleague.%20Nia%20DaCosta%20directed%20%26quot%3BThe%20Marvels.%26quot%3B%20Chloe%20Zhao%20directed%20%26quot%3BEternals.%26quot%3B%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20there%20are%20other%20signs%20of%20progress.%20According%20to%20USC's%20study%2C%20women%20directed%2014%25%20of%20the%20top%20100%20films%20in%202023%2C%20up%20from%2011%25%20of%20the%20top%20100%20films%20of%202022.%20It's%20a%20small%20but%20mighty%20cohort.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20maybe%20%26quot%3BBarbie%26quot%3B%20will%20help%20move%20the%20needle%20for%20new%2C%20original%20projects%20from%20here%20on%20out%20for%20more%20female%20creatives.%20It'll%20just%20happen%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Ftaylor-swift-barbie-movie-summer-girlhood-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eat%20a%20snail's%20pace%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbarbie-hasnt-resulted-in-film-industry-change-yet-2024-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704236041000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6594865cab6f2ebb11f8509d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbarbie-hasnt-resulted-in-film-industry-change-yet-2024-1%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%26quot%3BBarbie%26quot%3B%20led%20the%20box%20office%20in%202023%2C%20but%20new%20studies%20from%20USC%20and%20SDSC%20show%20opportunities%20still%20aren't%20as%20plentiful%20for%20women%20in%20Hollywood.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22kacuna%40businessinsider.com%20(Kirsten%20Acuna)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A258%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbarbie-hasnt-resulted-in-film-industry-change-yet-2024-1%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Trump%20challenges%20his%20'arbitrary'%20removal%20from%20Maine's%20ballot%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22