l%20religions%2C%20and%20said%20that%20the%20%E2%80%9Cguiding%20principle%20of%20Indian%20secularism%20democracy%E2%80%9D%20was%20%E2%80%9Calways%20to%20promote%20harmony%20and%20prosperity%20between%20all%20the%20diverse%20groups%20in%20our%20society%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20fact%2C%20in%20our%20society%20it%20makes%20more%20sense%20to%20speak%20of%20%E2%80%98diversities%E2%80%99%20instead%20of%20just%20%E2%80%98diversity%E2%80%99%20since%20they%20encompass%20faiths%20and%20beliefs%2C%20languages%20and%20cultural%20practices%2C%20regions%20and%20ecologies%2C%20histories%20and%20traditions%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20also%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20news%20agency%20also%20quoted%20her%20as%20questioning%20majoritarian%20interpretations%20of%20democracy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9C%E2%80%A6%20If%20a%20majority%20of%20people%20agree%2C%20can%20they%20always%20have%20a%20way%20over%20the%20remainder%3F%20What%20happens%20if%20the%20core%20interests%20of%20a%20small%20group%20are%20hurt%3F%20What%20is%20the%20remedy%20if%20a%20temporary%20majority%20insists%20on%20taking%20a%20decision%20which%20may%20have%20grave%20future%20consequences%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9COn%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20if%20an%20enduring%20but%20slim%20majority%20is%20formed%2C%20do%20they%20have%20the%20right%20to%20govern%20unchallenged%3F%E2%80%9D%20Gandhi%20asked.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20continued%3A%20%E2%80%9CIf%20people%20worry%20that%20their%20language%20or%20religious%20practice%20or%20way%20of%20life%20could%20be%20permanently%20threatened%20only%20because%20they%20were%20not%20many%20in%20number%2C%20it%20does%20not%20help%20peace%20or%20harmony%20in%20society.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGandhi%20also%20said%20that%20while%20people%20are%20familiar%20with%20concepts%20like%20secularism%20and%20democracy%2C%20the%20%E2%80%9Cdeep%20meaning%20behind%20these%20concepts%20are%20often%20elusive%E2%80%9D%2C%20adding%20that%20a%20%E2%80%9Cclear%20understanding%20of%